<DocsLayout title="Leci" description="Legislation backend — Brazilian statutes and regulations.">
  <h1>Leci</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Legislation backend</p>

  <span class="badge badge-alpha">alpha</span>

  <p>
    Leci is the legislation component of the sens.legal ecosystem. While Valter
    handles jurisprudence (how courts interpret the law), Leci will handle
    legislation (what the law actually says) — Brazilian statutes, regulations,
    and normative acts as a structured, searchable data source.
  </p>

  <p>
    When integrated with Valter, Leci will enable cross-referencing jurisprudence
    with the specific legislative provisions being applied, closing the loop between
    how courts interpret the law and what the law actually says.
  </p>

  <h2>Stack</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Astro + Starlight</li>
    <li><strong>Language:</strong> TypeScript</li>
    <li><strong>Planned backend:</strong> To be defined</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Planned Capabilities</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Structured Brazilian legislation database</li>
    <li>Version tracking of legislative changes over time</li>
    <li>Cross-reference with Valter's jurisprudence knowledge graph</li>
    <li>MCP tools for LLM access to legislation data</li>
    <li>REST API for frontend consumption</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Status</h2>

  <p>
    Leci is in the planning phase. The documentation site is live, but the
    legislation backend is not yet implemented. Integration with Valter is
    planned for v2.0 of the ecosystem.
  </p>

